summary:
The Security Council:
Recalling resolutions 1244 (1999) and 1345 (2001), and Presidential statements of 7 March 2001, 16 March 2001, and 13 August 2001, 
Welcoming steps by the Government of The former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia to consolidate a multi-ethnic society, 
Welcoming the Framework Agreement signed on 13 August 2001, 
Welcoming international efforts to prevent escalation of ethnic tensions and facilitate implementation of the Framework Agreement, 
1. Reaffirms commitment to sovereignty and territorial integrity of The former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia; 
2. Calls for full implementation of resolution 1345 (2001); 
3. Supports full and timely implementation of the Framework Agreement, rejects use of violence for political aims; 
4. Welcomes efforts of European Union and Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe; 
5. Endorses efforts of Member States and international organizations, supports multinational security presence; 
6. Demands safety of international personnel; 
7. Welcomes efforts of UN Interim Administration Mission in Kosovo and KFOR; 
8. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
